If a bad dump affects parts of the ROM that are never banked in or otherwise are never read in the course of operation, then yes, it is possible for ROMs to be functionally identical. Look at any ROM with a big string of $FF bytes, such as <em>Super Mario Bros. 2: Mario Madness</em>.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=9">tepples</a> — Mon May 28, 2007 9:22 pm</p><hr />
